Privacy Policy for iGain

Effective Date: June 12, 2025

Welcome to iGain. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit or use our services through our website and/or mobile applications (collectively, the "Platform"). Please read this policy carefully to understand our views and practices regarding your personal data.

1. Information We Collect
   We may collect and process the following data:

a. Personal Information

Full name
Email address
Profile image (optional)
Login provider ID (for Google or Facebook)
Account type (e.g., user, admin, content creator)
User preferences and notifications
Loyalty points (if applicable)
b. Authentication & Security

Password (hashed and encrypted)
Access tokens from OAuth providers (e.g., Google, Facebook)
OTP codes (temporary and hashed)
Device and session information
c. Usage Data

Pages visited and time spent
Course/content interactions
Feedback and support communications
d. Technical Data

IP address
Browser type and version
Operating system
Device identifiers 2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:

Register and manage your account
Provide secure login via email, Google, or Facebook
Deliver and personalize content or services
Improve the performance and features of the platform
Communicate with you (e.g., password reset, updates, promotions)
Analyze usage trends and optimize the user experience
Comply with legal obligations and protect user safety 3. Sharing of Information
We do not sell your personal data. However, we may share your information with:

Third-party service providers (e.g., email services, cloud storage)
Authentication providers (Google, Facebook) for login and access
Legal authorities when required by law or in response to legal processes
Business partners (if you opt-in) for joint service delivery or promotions 4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track activity on our platform and hold certain information. You can disable cookies via your browser settings, but some features may be affected.

5. Data Security
   We use industry-standard measures including encryption, token-based authentication, and access control to protect your data. Despite our efforts, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.

6. Your Rights
   Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights including:

Access to your personal data
Correction of incorrect or outdated data
Deletion of your account and associated data
Withdrawal of consent (where applicable)
You may exercise these rights by contacting us at [your email, e.g., support@igain.com].

7. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
   iGain does not knowingly collect or solicit data from anyone under the age of 13. If we learn that we have collected personal data from a child under 13, we will delete it promptly.

8. Changes to This Policy
   We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.

